Commentary: EDGED AND FOUR! Afridi is right on the money! Bowls a length ball around off, Latham is in two minds as to how to play the ball. He decides to play it off the back foot and manages to get a thick outside edge and the ball flies past the gully fielder and into the fence behind. New Zealand off the mark.
Length andÂ  outside off, left alone by Latham this time.

OUT! CAUGHT! Afridi strikes and Latham has to depart! Length and around off, Latham is still not sure whether to play off the front foot or the back foot as he hangs his bat out. The ball takes the outside edge and flies towards the third slip fielder. Azhar Ali there takes it on the second attempt and New Zealand have been dealt a blow early on in the innings.

A huge shout there from Afridi but nothing from the umpire. Fuller and around middle and leg, Williamson looks to tuck it to the leg side but gets beaten and out comes the appeal but the umpire is unmoved.
On a length and around off, Williamson turns it to short leg this time.

End of a brilliant first over from Afridi. He almost gets a second one. Length and slanting across the right-hander. Williamson has a feel for it as he pokes his bat out. Lucky for him the ball sneaks past the outside edge.
Abbas starts with a length ball around off, Blundell is aware of his off pole as he makes a confident leave.
Length ball around off, this time a bit closer to the sticks as Blundell blocks it off the front foot.
Good length and around off, Blundell defends it off the back foot towards short leg.
Short of a good length around off, Tom keeps it out off the back foot this time.

A huge shout from Abbas but the umpire is unmoved. Length ball around off, Blundell looks to defend it off the front foot but gets a huge inside edge onto his pads. The bowler though appeals but nothing from the umpire.
Ohhs and Ahhs from Pakistan players! Length ball around off, Blundell once again makes a confident leave. A maiden from Abbas.
Length and down the leg side, Kane lets it be.
Length ball around off, Kane blocks it out with an open stance.
Length and outside off, Williamson is not interested as he makes a leave now.
Another length ball around off and Kane makes another leave.
Full and around off, Kane bunts it to point this time.
Kane's off the mark with a brace! Full and around off, Williamson drives it through cover-point and gets a couple to open his account.
Length ball around off, Blundell defends it off the front foot to the off side this time.
Length and around off, Tom watches the ball closely before shouldering arms to it.
Fuller and around off, Blundell turns it to the leg side this time.
Blundell too gets off the mark! Fuller and around off, Tom plays with soft hands as he gets it past the gully fielder. The batsmen take a couple before the fielder mops it up.
BEATEN! So close to getting nicked! Length ball swinging away from the right hander. Blundell pokes at it tentatively only for the ball to go past the outside edge.
Length ball around off, Blundell lets it be this time.
Full and on the pads, Williamson turns it towards mid-wicket as the ball goes past the short leg fielder.
Just past the short leg fielder! Length ball around middle and leg, Blundell looks to flick it to the leg side but gets an inside edge. The ball lobs past the short leg fielder as they take a single.
Full and around off, Williamson drives it straight to the man at mid off.
Another fuller one this time and Kane pushes it to covers this time.
A short one from Afridi as Williamson ducks under it.
On a length and around off, Williamson looks to defend it off the front foot but gets an inside edge past the short leg fielder.
Good length delivery on middle, Blundell defends it off the back foot.
Back of a length on middle, Blundell looks to defend but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Good length delivery on off, Blundell keeps it out.
Length ball outside off, Blundell shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, Tom leaves it alone.
Back of a length on off, Blundell blocks it off the front foot.
Length and across the right-hander. Williamson looks to play at it initially but then decides to make a leave.
Another length ball outside off, Kane does not fiddle with it.
Length and outside off again, Williamson makes a leave as it is not in his hitting zone.
Length ball around off, Williamson blocks it solidly off the back foot now.

Beaten! Length and around off, Williamson looks to defend this one off the back foot but the ball swings past the defensive push of Kane. Lucky for Williamson and New Zealand that it did not kiss the outside edge.
Length and around off. Kane tucks it to the short leg fielder.
Length and down the leg side, Blundell looks to flick it but fails to get anything behind the ball.
Outside off now and Tom is happy to shoulder arms to it. New Zealand a bit cautious after that early blow.
Another length delivery outside off and Blundell comes on the front foot and then lifts his willow.
Good leave! Scrambled seam delivery from Abbas but it is outside off, Tom leaves it for the keeper to do the rest.
Fuller and around off, Tom now pushes it to point this time.
A touch straighter this time from Abbas as Blundell tucks it behind square on the leg side for a brace.

NOT OUT! Kane survives as Pakistan lose a review. Length ball around leg, Kane comes inside the line and looks to tuck it to the leg side. He though misses it as there is a sound when the ball went past him and into the mitts of the keeper. Rizwan behind the sticks is excited so are his teammates as they go up in an appeal. The umpire though does not entertain it as he shakes his head. Rizwan after consulting his players takes it upstairs as he signals 'T'. The replays roll it and it is a fair delivery as the Ultra Edge comes on now. Nothing on it when the ball is near the bat. Kane Williamson survives as Pakistan lose a review.

Full delivery on off, Williamson drives it towards covers for a single.
Good length delivery on off, Blundell defends it off the back foot.
Length ball on off, Blundell defends it off the back foot.

EDGED BUT JUST SHORT! Nice from Abbas but brilliant from Williamson. Abbas lands one around off as Williamson prods forward in defense. The ball though kisses the outside edge and goes towards second slip. As Kane played it with soft hands the ball dies in front of the fielder there.
Length and down the leg side, Kane looks to tickle it fine but fails to get bat on ball.

OUT! CAUGHT! Afridi bags a second one. He has been enjoying New Zealand conditions. New Zealand lose both their openers. Full and around off, inviting the batsman to go for the drive. Blundell obliges as he goes for the drive with no footwork and hard hands. He though could manage just to get a thickish outside edge that goes low towards Yasir Shah in the slips. Shah does well to go low and gobble the catch.

Another fuller one around middle, Taylor pushes it off the front foot towards the bowler.

Replays later show that the No ball saved Pakistan there. If they had reviewed then they would have lost it as there was a flat line on Ultra Edge when the ball went past the bat.

So close yet so far! Afridi was so close to getting his 4th wicket yet he is so far from getting it. Afridi nails in a perfect yorker on middle, Williamson who is camping on the back foot manages to get his bat down just in time. That ekes out a thickish bottom edge towards the leg side as the batsmen cross for a single. There is an appeal but nothing from the umpire. Mohammad Rizwan the skipper, ponders over taking a review but then decides against it. Replays later come in and it shows that it was pad first and later the Ball Tracker too shows three reds. Had Pakistan reviewed it they would have been overjoyed seeing the back of Kane Williamson. An opportunity goes begging.

OUT! CAUGHT! The short refreshment break does wonders for Pakistan. They were looking hapless with both Kane and Henry going about their business but the short drinks break has indeed brought some respite to the heat they were facing. Naseem finally gets into the wickets column. He goes short and around off, Henry Nicholls who is glued to the crease goes for the pull but fails to get it off the middle of the bat. He though takes his eyes off while playing and gets it off the glove. It lobs towards slips as the fielder takes it with ease. Replays later show that Nicholls was a bit unlucky there to not take the review. If he would have taken it then he could have been out there playing with his skipper as that ball came off his forearm and not the glove.

OUT! CAUGHT! It required a brilliant piece of fielding to remove Williamson! Brilliant stuff from Yasir Shah there, he delivers when his team needed it the most. A leg break tossed up around off, Kane comes on the front foot and looks to defend it but manages an outside edge in the process. The ball flies towards the lone slip there. Haris Sohail manning that position goes low to his right and gets his right hand out as the ball sticks in his palms. The Pakistan players rejoice it as the umpire converge and take it upstairs to check whether it is a clean catch or not. The soft signal being not out, the replays roll in and there was enough conclusive evidence to rule Kane Williamson out and the giant screen does flash out. Nevertheless, Williamson did his job for his team as he played a perfect captain's knock.

Fuller on off, kept out to short leg once again.
Another fuller one on off, Abbas plays it to gully.
Turn and bounce on that one! Floated on off, Abbas comes on the front foot to defend but the ball takes the outside edge and rolls towards point. A good first over from Santner.
Ali blocks it off the front foot.

OUT! CLEANED UP! Lovely piece of bowling. Bowls a fuller length ball around off, a hint of inward movement as Ali is stranded on the back foot. He looks to block it out but the ball does not come in as Ali expected. It though comes just enough to hit the top of off stump. Abid Ali's resistance finally comes to an end. New Zealand's new pace sensation Jamieson strikes once again.
Length and on off, defended to covers by Azhar.
Another length ball that climbs onto the batsman, Azhar Ali does well to take his bottom hand off as the ball goes towards point.
Fuller length ball on off, Ali pushes it to covers this time.
Another length ball on off, Ali defends it to mid on to see off Jamieson's over. A wicket maiden from him.

EDGY FOUR! Fuller and around off, Abbas stoops low to reach to the ball to defend it. He though gets an thick outside edge that goes past the gully fielder and into the third man fence. First boundary of the day.
Outside off, left alone.
Another length ball outside off, another leave from Abbas.
Full and angled on off, Abbas closes the face of the bat early as the ball goes off the outside edge towards point.
Short ball on off, Abbas sits under it.

OUT! CAUGHT! Boult finally has his man. The nightwatchman departs after some resistance. Boult lands one around off and gets it to shape away from the right hander. Abbas looks to defend it but ends up getting a thick outside edge which flies at a good height towards first slip where Ross Taylor takes the simplest of the catch.
Short and on midle, Ali ducks under it.
Length and angled across off, Ali lets it be.
Fuller and on off, Ali manages to push it to mid off.
Short and outside off, Ali watches it and then lifts his willow high up in the air to let the ball pass.
Another length ball outside off, Ali does not offer a stroke to it.
Full and on off, driven straight to the man at covers.
Length and outside off, Sohail taps it to gully.
Fuller and outside off, Sohail drives it through covers and gets a single. He gets off the mark too.
Short and on middle, Ali pulls it towards fine leg and gets off the mark with a single.
Fuller and on off, Haris pushes it to mid off this time.
Fuller and outside off, Sohail watches it and then decides not to play at it.
Length ball on off, Haris taps it to mid on this time.
Back of a length ball on middle, Ali plays it to mid-wicket.
Short one on leg, Ali looks to leave at it but fails to get away from the line of the ball as he gets hit on the tummy.
Back of a length ball on off, Ali taps it to mid off now.
Length and outside off, no shot offered by Azhar Ali.
Another fuller length ball outside off, Ali comes on the front foot and tries to do a Smithsque leave.
Another length ball and outside off too, Ali is happy to leave it for the keeper.
BEATEN! Length and around off, Haris stays on the back foot as he looks to defend it. The ball though shapes away from him and goes to the keeper. Lucky that he did not edge that one.
Outside off, left alone this time.
Another away swinger from Boult as Haris lets it be.
Fuller and on off, Haris taps it to mid off.
Short and on off, Sohail reads it early and then sits under it.
Fuller and outside off, Haris opens the face of the bat and guides it past point for a single.
Length and on the pads, tucked towards mid-wicket for a single.
Fuller on off, driven to mid off by Azhar Ali.
Outsde off, Ali makes a leave to this one.
Length ball on the pads, Ali clips it past short fine leg and gets a single this time.
Length and outside off, Sohail makes a leave now.
BOUNCER! Short and on middle, Haris does well to sit under it.
Fuller on off, pushed off the front foot towards mid on.
Length and around off, Ali makes a leave to this one.
Length and outside off, Ali covers his sticks and then makes a leave.
On a length and on middle, Ali turns it to mid on this time.
Length and across the right hander, Ali lets it be.
Full and on middle, Ali clips it past mid on and in the gap for a single.
Length ball on middle, Ali clips it towards deep mid-wicket and gets a brace.
Full on off, driven with a straight bat to mid on.
Length and outside off, further moves away after pitching as Ali makes a leave.
Length and outside off, Ali lets it be.
Another length ball outside off, Ali is happy to not play at it.
Fuller and on off, Ali plays it with an angled bat towards cover-point.
Good length and around off, Sohail shoulders arms to this one.
Fuller length and outside off, Sohail watches the ball sails through to the keeper as he does not offer any shot.
Fuller and on off, Haris taps it to gully.
Length and on off, Haris plays it to covers.
Length ball but this time closer to off but not close enough to make Haris play.
Fuller on off, Haris plays it to mid off to see off the Wagner over.
Length on off, pushed off the back foot to the mid on.

OUT! CAUGHT! Southee gets a wicket finally. Length ball angled across the off stump, Azhar Ali who is camping on the back foot looks to push it to the off side. He though gets it to play with an angled bat but fails to do so. The ball goes to the keeper where Watling collects it and goes up in an appeal. The umpire though is not interested. Kane Williamson signals 'T'. Let's see what the replays have to say. It is a legal delivery as the Ultra Edge comes on. It shows a little spike when the ball goes past the bat. The on-field call is overturned as Azhar Ali has to take the long walk back.
Length ball on off, played to mid on by Alam.
Alam is off the mark as he tucks this length ball on the pads to square leg for a single.
On a length and on off, pushed to mid off this time.

OUT! CAUGHT! Pakistan suddenly falling apart here! With half the side gone and still 379 runs away from the New Zealand's score Pakistan are in deep waters. Southee gets his second wicket. Fuller and around off, Sohail looks to drive it away from the body as he pushes at it. He though fails to get it off the meat of the bat as the thick outside edge flies towards gully where Henry Nicholls does well to get low and pouch the catch.
On a good length on middle, tucked towards mid-wicket for a quick single.
Outside off, Rizwan shoulders arms to this one.
A good length ball on off and middle, the skipper pushes it back to the bowler. Wagner sees Rizwan outside his crease and looks to hit the stumps but he misses.
Length on off, Rizwan pushes it towards the point region.

FOUR! The skipper opens his account with a good shot! Pakistan will need his positive tempo if they want to add some valuable runs to this total! On a length on off, Rizwan creams this drive through the cover region to find the ropes.
Short and on off, pulled to the deep square leg region for a brace.
On off, pushed back to Tim.
Outside off, no shot offered to this by Alam.
Around the off pole on a good length, tucked to the square leg region as Alam looks for the run. Rizwan, though, is not interested and sends him back.
Just around the off pole, Alam pushes this towards mid off.
A single this time as this good length ball around off is tucked towards square leg by Fawad.
On off, pushed to mid on. Just the single off this over.
Length delivery around off, tapped towards the off side and no is the call straightaway by Alam for the single.
Same delivery as the last ball, same shot offered by Alam. Another loud no for the single by Fawad.
On off, tapped to point. Fawad is comfortable in his crease as he denies the single again.
Good length and around off, pushed to the cover region. 'No, no', Fawad says, for the single again.

NOT OUT! This was a very close call but good running on the part of Alam has ensured that he does not lose his wicket. Short and on middle, pulled to the fine leg region. The batters take one but Alam wants another. He runs back and Rizwan is forced to go for the double. The throw is at the keeper's end and Watling whips the bails off quickly, as Alam dives in. The third umpire is called into play. Replays roll in and you can see Alam's bat grounded as the bails are off. Alam survives.
On middle, flicked to the leg side. THAT WILL BE LUNCH ON DAY 3!
Fuller and on off, Rizwan drives it off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
Jamieson is bowling thunderballs there! Short of a length ball on off, Rizwan looks to defend it but gets hit on the glove as his bottom hand comes off.
Fuller and around off, Rizwan defends it to covers.
Length and around off, Rizwan tucks it towards square leg and gets a single. First run off the session.
Back of a length ball outside off, Alam lets the ball through to the keeper.
Another length ball outside off, Alam leaves it in an unorthodox manner.
Full and outside off, driven by Rizwan but straight to the man at mid off.

In the air... Just Short! Fuller and on off, Rizwan looks to drive it through the off side but gets it off the inner half of the bat. The ball lobs towards mid on where the fielder tries to go for the catch but it falls just short of him.
Length ball outside off, RizwanÂ does not play at it.
Fuller and on off, driven towards mid on.
Full and on off, Rizwan drives only to find short cover to perfection.
Good length ball outside off, Rizwan lets this one through to the keeper. A maiden from Wagner.
Length ball on off, Alam plays it to covers.
Length ball outside off, Alam leaves it the Steven Smith way.
Short and on middle, Alam does well to sit under it.
Another short one and Fawad does the same thing as the previous delivery. Sits under it.
Full and on middle, keeping low too. Alam does well to push it back to the bowler.
On a length and around off, Alam looks to play it to the on side but at the last instance gets it towards gully. The ball went off the glove this time.
Good length and outside off, Rizwan takes a step forward before leaving it for the keeper.
Length and on off, pushed to short cover off the front foot by Rizwan.
Slower yorker outside off, Rizwan pushes it to mid off this time.
Short of good length angling into the batsman, Rizwan hops and plays it to point.

Cut away and cut away well! Short of length ball outside off, Rizwan cuts it through point but the timing is not there on that shot. The ball will not reach the fence as it gets fielded in the deep. A couple taken.
Outside off, left alone.
Length and angled on off, Fawad taps it to mid on this time.
Fuller on off, driven towards mid on where the fielder puts in a dive to save some runs.
Length and around off, Alam gets hurried into the shot as he pushes it to the leg side.
On the pads, Alam clips it to mid-wicket now.
Fuller on off, Alam taps it to mid on.
BOUNCER! Short and on middle, Alam sits under it with ease.
Fuller on off, Rizwan strokes it to mid off.
Outside off, Rizwan watches the ball as it goes past him.

FOUR! Positive signs! The skipper taking the charge here. Full and outside off, Rizwan comes on the front foot and then drives it past the man at mid off. Once it beats the man there, it goes onto meet the boundary ropes at long off.
Short and on middle, Rizwan pulls it to mid-wicket for a single.
Short and wide outside off, Alam who is standing on the leg stump line comes towards the off pole once the ball is delivered and then cuts it to cover-point.
Fuller and on off, Alam pushes it off the inside half of the bat to mid on.
Full and on off, Rizwan strokes it to the man at mid off.
Fuller once again, Rizwan dead bats it towards mid off.
Short and on middle, Rizwan pulls it to square leg this time.
On a length and on middle, Rizwan pushes it to the leg side.
Fuller in length from Jamieson, Rizwan strokes it from the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
Fuller and on off, Rizwan pushes it to covers.
Short and on middle, Alam pulls it through square leg and gets just a single this time.
Length ball on off, Rizwan taps it to covers.
Length ball on the pads, Rizwan tucks it to square leg and gets to the other end with a single.
On the pads of Alam now, Fawad tucks it towards deep square leg for a single.
Full and on off, Rizwan drives it uppishly but it drops just short of the fielder at short cover.
On a length and outside off, Rizwan lets it be.
On a length and on off, Alam taps it to covers. He though gets a bit squared up there.
On a length and on off, Alam tucks it to the leg side this time.
Short of length ball on off, Alam pushes it away from the body towards covers.
On a length and on off, Alam turns it to the leg side now.
Short and on off, Fawad pulls it but finds the man at mid-wicket.
Another short one and Alam does well to pull it but fails to pierce the gap at mid-wicket.
Length ball on off, Rizwan pushes it back to the bowler.
Another fuller length ball on off, Rizwan strokes it to covers.
Full on off, Rizwan mistimes the drive to mid off this time.
Length and on the pads, Rizwan comes inside the line and then flicks it to fine leg. He gets a brace this time.
Length and on middle, Rizwan gets right behind the ball to defend it.
On a length and on off, Rizwan drives it only to find mid off there.
Full toss on middle, tucked to the mid-wicket region.
Back of a length and on middle, Rizwan hops and tucks it to square leg. Looks for the single but decides not to go for it.
On off, blocked.
On a length outside off, some inward movement noticed as Rizwan raises his blade to let this one through.
Short of a length and on off, Rizwan nudges this one to the leg side for a quick run.
Outside off, Fawad cuts this one to the gully region where the fielder dives and makes a good stop.

A bumper by Wagner! Bowls a short one on middle, Rizwan swats this one to the mid-wicket region but it is just short of the man there. The Kiwis are setting up a trap as the leg side is packed and Wagner will be peppering Rizwan with short balls.
Short on middle, pulled to the leg side again.
Another short one on the ribs, Rizwan pulls but finds the man at square leg.
Bumper on middle, ducked under by Rizwan.
Short on middle, Rizwan sits under this one.
Short of a length and on off, pulled to square leg. A maiden to Wagner's name.
On a length on middle, tucked to the leg side and Alam looks for the single. The fielder there collects and has a shy at the non-striker's end but misses. In the end, a single taken.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
Length ball on off, Rizwan works it to the mid off region.
Length and on off, pushed to the off side for a single.
Length and on leg, flicked to fine leg for a single.
Length and on off, Rizwan looks to defend it but gets beaten to wear the blow on the thigh pad.

OUT! CAUGHT! Wagner peppering Alam with short deliveries does the trick! Another one falls for the visitors and things not going to plan for the Men in Green! On a shorter length and on middle, Alam looks to pull but misses. The ball, though, nicks the bat and goes towards Watling who takes a good catch. The players appeal loudly and the umpire obliges by raising his finger. Alam does not opt for the review and just walks off. Pakistan are in a spot of bother and will need something miraculous if they need to avoid the follow-on.
Bumper on middle to start off with for Ashraf, who ducks under this one.
Another short one on middle, pulled to the fine leg region for one.
Rizwan leaves this delivery as it was down the leg side.
Same delivery as this was down the leg side again, but this time, Rizwan attempts to pull, he misses though.
Short of a length on leg, Rizwan thinks about leaving but the ball hits him on his back and rolls to the leg side. Nasty, that. Must have hurt. But the skipper should be fine to continue.
On off, blocked.

BEATEN! BEAUTY! That's what that was! Boult is looking menacing now! On a length around the off pole, straigtens a touch after pitching, Ashraf looks to play at this but the ball just about misses his outside edge and into Watling's mitts.
Length on off, pushed to the point region for one.
Short and around off, pulled towards the mid on region.
Good shot but the fielding is also very good! Length ball outside off, Rizwan drives this one to the cover region where Latham dives and makes a good stop.
On off, blocked out.
Short and on middle, Ashraf looks to play the pull but the ball does not rise at Faheem expected. In the end, he fends it away.
Length and down the leg side, Ashraf lets it be.
FOUR! Not high enough from Wagner and Ashraf commits to the shot and sends it past the ropes! On a shorter length on middle, pulled to the deep square leg region to find the ropes.
On middle, blocked.
Short and on middle, pulled to the fine leg region for one.
WIDE! A short one on middle, left alone by Rizwan. The umpire indicates a wide for the height.
On middle, pulled to fine leg for a single.
On off, pushed to mid off.
Back of a length and on off, tapped to point. No is the call for the single by Rizwan.
On off, nudged to square leg for one.
FOUR! Faheem picks up another boundary! On a fuller length on middle, Faheem just clips this one through the short fine leg region and the ball runs away to the ropes.
Good length on off, Ashraf pushes it to the leg side.
On middle, flicked to fine leg for one more single to end the over.
Short in length and around the middle pole, pulled by Ashraf to deep square leg for a single.
On off, blocked out.
Short ball on middle, MH sits under this one.
Another bouncer on middle and leg, Rizwan does what he did on the last ball, ducks under this one.
Short on middle, Rizwan seems to have decided to leave these balls alone, sits under this one too.
Bouncer on middle, ducked under by Rizwan again.
Length and outside off, Ashraf shoulders arms to this one.
Full on off, Faheem drives it uppishly towards covers where it falls short of Tom Latham.
Length and down the leg side, Ashraf misses his flick and the keeper to fails to collect it cleanly. The batters take a bye.
Length delivery outside off, Rizwan lifts his bat and lets it be.
Another length ball outside off, another leave by Rizwan.
On a length around off, Rizwan punches it towards covers and gets a single.
Down the leg side, Rizwan misses his flick.
On middle, pushed to the mid on region.
A full delivery around the off pole, Rizwan clips this one through mid-wicket to collect a brace. 100 up for Pakistan as well. They still trail by 331 runs.
In the channel around off on a good length, worked towards the square leg region for a single. They think about the second but settle for one in the end.
Outside off, Faheem plays this uppishly through the point region for a couple.
Outside off again, nothing doing says Faheem as he lets this one go.
Good length on off, pushed to the off side.
Short of a length outside off, Rizwan gets on top of the bounce and punches this one through the cover region for a brace.
Shorter in length and on middle, MR pulls this to deep square leg for just the single this time.

SIX! Faheem has looked good so far and he scores his first biggie of this inning! He also moves onto 21 from 20 balls. Slightly short and on middle, Ashraf pulls this one over the deep square leg fence for a maximum.
Outside off, left alone.
A full ball on middle, well dug out by Ashraf.
Fuller and on off, Rizwan pushes it back to the bowler off the front foot.
Full and around off, pushed to short cover this time.

Lovely shot! Nothing doing! Full and straight on off, Rizwan drives it with the straightest of the bat but hits the stumps at the other end. A millimeter here or there and that could have been a boundary.
On middle, flicked to mid-wicket for a single.
On off, Ashraf pushes it to short cover.
Fuller length ball outside off, Faheem strokes it to cover-point. Just a single from this over.
Full and angled on off, Rizwan blocks it right under his eyes.
Another length ball on off, Rizwan taps it but the ball bounces a bit as Rizwan tries to get it away from the stumps.
Full and on off, Rizwan drives it only to get an inside edge towards square leg for a single.
Length and on off, Ashraf drops it to covers with soft hands there.
Fuller and on the pads, Faheem flicks it through fine leg and gets a single now.
Full and on off, driven powerfully down the ground where Boult fields in his followthrough.
On a length and on off, Ashraf taps it to covers.
A tough chance though! Fuller and around off, Ashraf drvies it uppishly towards short cover where the fielder gets his hands to the ball but fails to hold onto it.
On off, blocked to the off side.
Another length ball around off, Ashraf blocks it out.
Back of length ball on off, Ashraf drives it to cover-point.
On off, pushed to covers by Ashraf to see off the over from Southee.
Short and around off, Rizwan punches it through covers and gets a single.
Back of a length ball on off, Faheem taps it to covers now.
Fuller and on off, Ashraf is happy to push it to covers off the back foot.
FOUR! CRACKED! Short and wide outside off, Ashraf gets into the position early as he punches it through cover-point. The ball races to the fence in a jiffy.
FOUR! Back-to-back hits to the fence. Short and on middle, Ashraf swivels and pulls it behind square on the leg side. The ball beats the fielder there to reach the fence.
Short and outside off, Ashraf lets it be.
FOUR! Rizwan joins the party! Short and on middle, Rizwan pulls it through square leg, just past the square leg umpire, who does well to get out of the way and he gets a boundary.
Length and outside off, tapped to the off side.
Length and outside off, Rizwan lets it go.
FOUR! Beautiful shot! Full and on off, Rizwan drives it straight and past the bowler. The ball races to the fence. That also brings the 50-run stand between the two. A much needed one though.
On off, pushed to covers for a single.
Outside off, Ashraf makes a leave.
Back of a length ball on off, Rizwan taps it to the off side and rotates the strike with a single.
Full and on off, Ashraf dead bats it towards covers.
FOUR! SMASHED! Short and on middle, sits up nicely for Ashraf to bring out the pull and nail to towards deep mid-wicket as the ball crosses the fence for a boundary.
Length and on leg, Ashraf misses his flick as the ball goes towards square leg off his pads. A leg bye is what the batsmen get.
Full on off, pushed to covers this time by Rizwan.
Full and aiming at the stumps, angling in too, Rizwan strokes it to mid on. Pakistan in counter-attacking mood.
Fuller and on off, Ashraf blocks it with a straight bat to mid off.
Another fuller length ball around off, Ashraf keeps it out off the front foot.
On a length and angling into off, Ashraf dead bats it back to the bowler.
Slow and swinging from Wagner as Ashraf goes for a drive. He though misses it as he keeper collects it by going low to his left.
On off, kept out.
Length ball on off, Ashraf plays it off the back foot.
Full and around off, Rizwan drives but finds the man at mid off.
FOUR! Cut away! Short and wide outside off, Rizwan pounces onto it as he cuts it through point and gets a boundary to his name. He moves onto 46 now.
Short and on off, pulled to square leg for a single.
On off, pushed back to the bowler.
On off, punched to the mid off region.
Good length around off, pushed to the point region to collect a single.
Floated on off, pushed back to the bowler.
Tossed up and spinning into Ashraf, Faheem makes room and strokes it to point.
Turn and bounce! Tossed up ball outside off, Ashraf lets it go through to keeper who fails to collect it. The ball goes to fine leg as the batters take a couple of byes.
Flatter on off, Faheem punches it through covers and takes a run.
Floated around off, Rizwan drives it through covers and takes a single this time.
On off, tapped to point.
Full and on off, Rizwan pushes it off the higher part of the bat towards mid off.
Another fuller length ball around off, Rizwan strokes it to mid off once again.

FIFTY FOR MOHAMMAD RIZWAN! Short and outside off, Rizwan cuts it through cover-point. Santner in the deep does well to keep the batsmen down to two runs. Rizwan gets to his half ton too. A well deserved and an important knock from the skipper of Pakistan. His 4th fifty in Tests as well.
Length and on off, Rizwan taps it to covers.
On off, watchfully defended.
Length on off, kept out off the back foot.
Tossed up on off, Ashraf defends it out.
Darts one on off, Faheem blocks it.
Flatter outside off, Faheem punches it through covers and gets a single.
Floated on off, driven straight to short cover.
Loopy on off, cut straight to sweeper cover for a single by Rizwan.
Floated on middle, Ashraf comes right behind the line of the ball to block it.
Short and angled across the right hander, Rizwan ducks under it.
Another short one outside off, Rizwan leaves it again.
Length and on the pads, Rizwan strokes it through square leg for a brace.
Short and on middle, Rizwan pulls it but finds mid-wicket.
This time he finds the gap as he pulls this short one through mid-wicket and gets a couple of runs.
On off, pushed to mid off.
Tossed up on off, pushed to short mid-wicket.
Loopy on off, defended right near the boots by Ashraf.
Tossed up on off, kept out.
Floated on off, pushed to covers.
Flatter on off, Ashraf pulls it to deep mid-wicket for a couple.
Tossed up outside off, left alone by Ashraf.
SLASH AND A MISS! Back of a length outside off, the bounce got a bit big on Rizwan as he looked to cut but misses it.
FOUR! Anything short and Rizwan has decided that he will disptach those. Pulls this one to the deep square leg region for a boundary.
A full ball around the leg pole, Rizwan looks for the flick but misses and Watling does well to dive to his left and stop this one.
On off, blocked.
Length and on middle, nudged to the square leg region.
On off, kept out by Rizwan.
On a good length on off, Ashraf drives this one nicely but finds the man at mid off.
Outside off, Ashraf has no issues in leaving this one alone.
Another length ball outside off, well left by Faheem.
PLAY AND A MISS! On a length around off, Ashraf wants to have a bite of this but misses it completely.
Outside off, Faheem raises his blade to let this one through.
A length delivery on middle, tucked away to the mid-wicket fielder. Pakistan are building up a good partnership, as this one reaches 83 runs.
On off, pushed to the mid on region.
Back of a length and on the pads, Rizwan clips this one to the fine leg region to rotate the strike. Rizwan wanted two but had to settle for the single.
Length outside off, well driven by Faheem but he finds the cover fielder. Solid shot but no result for Ashraf.
Outside off, plays it to the point region.
On off, pushed to the off side.

EDGY FOUR! Boult got what he wanted but this evaded everyone and ran away to the ropes. He dishes a back of a length ball around off, nips away after pitching, Faheem looks to block it out but the ball takes the outside edge and goes past the slip cordon and into the ropes.
On off, pulled to fine leg for one.
Length delivery around the off pole, Ashraf is solid in his defense.

An appeal for LBW but no says the umpire! A back of a length ball on off and middle, Ashraf looks to tuck it away but misses to get hit on the pads. The players appeal but nothing from the umpire. They will not go for the review as they do not think it will fetch them the result that they want. Might have been an inside edge on this one and even the height could have been an issue so good decision from the umpire and also the Kiwis, to not take a review.
On middle, tucked to square leg.
On off, blocked out.
On a good length outside off, Ashraf cuts this one but finds the point fielder. A good over by Tim. Just one run off it.
A full ball on middle, Rizwan digs it out towards the mid on region.
Outside off, punched to the point region.

EDGED...SAFE AND FOUR! Another edge and this one races away to the ropes. Southee is the culprit! A back of a length delivery around off, Rizwan plays this one late and can only induce an outside edge. It flies just past Southee at third slip and runs away to the third man boundary. Could have got the big wicket of the skipper but it was not meant to be.
Good length on off, MR drives it nicely to covers.
On middle, kept out.
Outside off, left alone by Rizwan.
On off, worked to the leg side for a brace.
Outside off, Ashraf shoulders arms to this one.
Outside off, Ashraf lets it through to the keeper again.
Good length ball on off, well kept out.

FOUR! Boult puts in a dive in the deep but it is not enough to save the ball from crossing the ropes. A full length ball on middle, Ashraf flicks this one to the fine leg region and it goes past the diving Trent into the ropes. Ashraf moves to 49 with that stroke.
On off, blocked out.
Yorker on off, dug out back towards Boult.
On a good length on off, Rizwan pushes this to the off side.

100-RUN PARTNERSHIP UP BETWEEN THESE TWO! It has been a brilliant partnership and it was something that the visitors needed! They were in at a tough stage and have done well to stay out there and battle it out with the Kiwi pacers. A short one on middle, pulled by Rizwan to deep mid-wicket for one.

FIFTY FOR FAHEEM ASHRAF. Just what the doctor ordered and Ashraf has delivered when his team has needed him the most! A back of a length ball and on off, Ashraf drops it to the cover region for a quick single. Some appreciation from his skipper and his teammates are up and clapping. A well deserved half-century.
Full and on middle, pushed to mid off.
On off, pushed to point.
Length and on off, Ashraf blocks it out.

He hits the bull's eye and New Zealand start celebrating as the umpire takes it upstairs. Replays roll in and it shows that Rizwan who is running to the danger end is short of his ground despite putting a desparate dive. This could be the opening that New Zealand wanted.

Pakistan lose their 8th wicket and it seems that they will might lose all their wickets before the end of play. A good length ball on off, nipping into the right-hander, Yasir looks to fend it away but misses and the ball goes through his defense and goes onto rattle the stumps behind him.

OUT! CAUGHT! WAGNER SETS THE TRAP AND COMPLETES THE JOB! He keeps pepperingÂ Afridi with short stuff and finally has his man. This one is again on the shorter side and on leg, Afridi looks to evade it by pushing at it but the ball takes the glove and lobs to short leg who takes the catch.

FOUR! Faheem is looking for his hundred now! A short one and on off, AshrafÂ pulls this one to the deep mid-wicket region and it crosses the ropes on the bounce for a boundary. Moves to 91.

OUT! CAUGHT! It was not meant to be for him but he should be proud off the innings that he has played! He knew that the end was near and was looking to get his hundred but he falls in the process. On a length around off, Ashraf looks to have a poke at this but can only induce an outside edge, which goes towards Watling and he does not drop these chances. PAKISTAN END THEIR FIRST INNINGS ON 239. TRAILING BY 192 RUNS!

Latham and New Zealand are underway on Ball one of Day 4. Afridi starts with a full ball outside off, Latham drives it to cover where the fielder fumbles, allowing the batters to cross over for the single.

NOT OUT! There is nothing conclusive about whether there was bat on it or not. Pakistan will not be happy. Good length ball around off, Blundell looks to defend but seems to have missed it. He gets rapped on the pads. Pakistan put up an appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Pakistan think of a review and take it in the end. Afridi is fine on the front foot but the Ultra Edge and the replays state that there is nothing conclusive if there was bat or not. So, the on-field decision stays. Pakistan lose a review.

What happened there? A length ball on the pads, Fawad looks to work it on the leg side but misses to get hit on the pad. The ball goes just wide of the leg pole.
He gets solid behind the line this time to defend it out. And Wagner once again oversteps.
Good length and on the pads, Fawad takes a blow high on his pad.
Fuller and around off, Rizwan strokes it towards mid off.
Another solid front foot block from Rizwan.
Good length and on middle, Rizwan works it through square leg for a run.
Banged short and around off, defended by Fawad.
Good length and around middle, worked towards the man at forward short leg.
Full and around off, flicked towards mid-wicket for nothing.
Darted outside off, Rizwan lets it be. Looks like it hit the flat of the pad there as the Kiwis appealed but nothing from the umpire.
Floated on middle and leg, Rizwan looks to defend but it turns in and takes the inside edge. The ball races towards the fine leg fence but the fielder chases it down. They take three.
Flatter and on middle, worked on the leg side.
Quicker one around middle, this time Alam tucks it through mid-wicket for one.
Short and wide outside off, pushed towards the man at cover.
Tossed up and around off, spins away as Rizwan defends it off his back foot.
Wagner bangs it short and it is on middle and leg, Fawad this time goes for the pull. He mistimes it towards short fine leg.
Bouncer on middle, this time Alam ducks.
Length and around off, kept out.

Risky run! Direct hit and it would've been close. A fuller ball around off and middle, Alam works it towards square leg and calls for a run. Rizwan responds but starts a little late. The fielder picks the ball quickly and has a shy at the striker's end but he misses as Rizwan dives to make his crease.
Fuller and around off, pushed back to the bowler.
Outside off, left alone.
Tossed up around off, kept out by Alam.
Loopy ball outside off, Fawad defends it off his front foot.
Drags it short and it is on middle, Alam pulls it down to deep mid-wicket for one.
Loops it up and bowls it wide outside off, it is stroked to mid off nicely by Rizwan.
On middle, pushed back to Santner.
Beauty to end the over! Tossed up and around off, Rizwan is drawn forward as he looks to defend. However, the ball spins away, past the outside edge.
Good stop by Southee. Shortish and around middle and leg, Fawad tucks it to the left of Southee at square leg. The Kiwi pacer dives and stops the ball to keep Fawad on strike.
A bumper! Fawad ducks under it.
Outside off, left alone.
Shortish ball on the pads, Alam looks to leave but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Short and wide, Fawad slams it through point. The fielder gives it a chase and gets two. Should've got three there but they just didn't go for it. The stand between the two moves to 49.

FOUR! TAKE THAT! Enough of blocking and ducking to these bumpers says Fawad and slams this short ball wide of the diving square leg fielder. No one is in the deep so it races down to the fence. Alam is into the 40s.
Full and around off, pushed to mid off.
Tossed up and outside off, driven to cover-point for nothing.
Flatter and around off, turned towards the leg side.
Floated full and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Tossed up and outside off, it is driven to the left of the cover fielder. They go for the run as Williamson throws the ball to the keeper.
Floated on middle, worked on the leg side.
Banged short and Rizwan pulls. It goes to deep square leg for one.
FOUR! Hammered! Dismissive from Fawad. Short and just outside off, Fawad hammers the pull wide of the man at mid-wicket for a boundary.
Bumper down the leg, Alam lets it be.
Short again. This one is around middle. Fawad ducks again.
Short again and this time Fawad pulls it down to deep mid-wicket for one.
Fuller and around off, pushed towards the cover region.
Full and on middle, flicked to mid-wicket for nothing.
On off, pushed back to the bowler this time.
Floated outside off, Fawad comes on the front foot to block.
Full and on middle, flicked wide of the man at mid on and they go for the single. The fielder fails to pick up the ball cleanly.
Tossed up and around off, a solid front foot defense from the Pakistani skipper.
On off, Rizwan keeps it out.
Banged short and around off, Alam ducks under it.
Short and outside off, Fawad has no business with it again.
Wagner goes full this time. Fawad keeps it out.
Short and around off and middle, Fawad sits under it one more time.
Slower fuller ball this time. Fawad works it towards mid on and gets to the other end.
Good length and around off, Rizwan defends it off the back foot. With that, it is Lunch on Day 5.
Santner starts with a flatter ball outside off, Alam punches it to deep cover for a single.
BEATEN! That's what Santner is looking for. Loopy ball outside off, spinning away. Rizwan looks to defend but fails to get any bat on it.
Quicker on off, Rizwan defends it out off the back foot.
Tossed up on middle, Rizwan prods forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Tossed up on middle, Rizwan flicks it to square leg for a single.
FIFTY! Excellent innings so far from Fawad Alam! This is a very important innings from the left-hander. Tossed up on middle, Fawad tucks it to deep square leg for a single.
Short ball around middle, Alam ducks under it.
Back of a length ball on off, Alam taps it to gully off the back foot.
Almost chopped on! Brilliant delivery from Jamieson! Short ball around off, Alam looks to duck at first but the ball does not rise as enough. It takes the inside edge and goes past the stumps.
Fullish ball on middle and leg, Fawad tucks it to mid-wicket.
Good length ball outside off, Alam leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle, Fawad tucks it to mid-wicket for a dot.
Full and outside off, Rizwan drives it wide of mid off for a single.
Loopy ball on the pads, Alam flicks it uppishly but wide of the fielder for a single.
Tossed up outside off, Rizwan lunges forward and drives it to cover for another run.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Tossed up around off, Alam pads it away. Santner appeals but the umpire is not interested. The Kiwi players discuss among themselves whether to take the review but decide against it.
FOUR! Nicely played! Too short from Santner! He bowls it outside off, Alam cuts it through the cover-point region for a boundary.
FOUR! This is poor bowling from Santner! He bowls it short again on middle, Fawad camps on his back foot and then pulls it to deep square leg for a boundary. 150 up for Pakistan.
PLAY AND A MISS! Good length ball outside off, Rizwan looks to cut but the ball goes to the keeper. Jamieson has overstepped. No Ball signalled.
Good length ball down the leg side, Rizwan looks to flick but misses.
Back of a length ball on off, Rizwan is solid in defense.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Good length ball the pads, Rizwan looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads. Jamieson puts up an appeal but the umpire is unmoved. Rizwan seems to have injured himself but is fine to continue.
On middle, this is worked to square leg for a single.
Good length ball on middle, Fawad blocks it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on middle, tucked to square leg.
Flatter ball outside off, Rizwan punches it to cover-point for a single.
EDGY! Floated ball on off, Alam looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes past the first slip fielder for a single.
Flatter ball on the pads, Rizwan looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Tossed up on middle, defended back to the bowler.
Short ball down the leg side, Rizwan looks to pull but misses. Watling whips the bails off but Rizwan was in.
Tossed up outside off, Rizwan pushes it to cover.
On off, defended out.
Length ball on off, defended solidly.
Shortish around off, pushed in the gap at point for a brace.
Close! A fuller ball outside off, Fawad looks to fend but misses and the ball goes through to the keeper. An appeal is made by the keeper but nothing from the umpire.
Length around off, blocked solidly by Alam.
Length on off, Alam gets behind that and blocks it.
Flatter around off, poked towards point.
Flatter around middle, defended solidly by Rizwan.
Fuller around off, tucked towards covers.
Flatter around off, played straight to covers by Rizwan.
Flatter on the pads, Rizwan looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the thigh pad.
Quicker ball on middle, Rizwan prods forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Very full on middle, Alam pokes that towards point.
Length ball around middle, defended solidly by Alam.
Length ball on middle, Alam blocks this out.
Length around off, pushed towards cover.
Slightly short around off, Alam cut its straight to point.

Almost chops it on his stumps! Fawad is lucky here. A short ball just outside off, Fawad looks to punch but gets an inside edge. The ball goes towards leg gully. The fielder has a shy at the bowler's end but he misses. It was a needless throw and there is no one to back it up. They run two more.
Floated on the pads, Alam plays it to short leg. Santner has overstepped. No Ball given.
Flatter outside off, Alam cuts it though point for a single.
Outside off, left alone by Rizwan.
Tossed up on off, Rizwan guides it to first slip.
Quicker on middle, Rizwan defends it back to the bowler.
Shortish and outside off, Rizwan cuts it straight to point.
Loopy ball outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
Good length ball on middle, Alam defends it out.
Fullish ball on middle, Alam pushes it towards mid on.
Full ball on off, Alam blocks it to the bowler.
Short ball outside off, Fawad cuts but finds the gully fielder. Good effort from Nicholls there.
Full ball on the pads, Alam works it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan defends it back to the bowler.
Too short from Santner! He bowls it outside off, Alam goes on his back foot and then punches it to deep cover for a single.
Loopy ball on middle, Rizwan prods forward and defends it back to the bowler.
Drifter from Santner, Rizwan is solid in defense.
Full on the pads, Rizwan once again plays it back to the bowler.
A couple now! Santner once again bowls it short and this one is on off, Rizwan punches it through the covers for a couple.
Tossed up on middle and leg, Rizwan defends it onto the pitch.
Length ball around off, defended back to the bowler.
Length around off, Alam hits it towards point and gets a single.
Almost gets the edge! A length ball pitched around off, hits a crack and shapes away from the batsman. Rizwan goes for the drive but gets beaten comprehensively there.
Length ball aroundÂ off, Rizwan defends it solidly.
Similar ball around off, Rizwan covers the stumps and blocks it.
Fuller and around off and middle, driven to mid on for nothing by Rizwan.
Flatter ball outside off, Alam plays it to cover.
Quicker on off, pushed towards mid off.
Shorter and outside off, Alam cuts it straight to point.
Tossed up on middle, Alam works it back to the bowler.
Floated ball on middle, Alam tucks it to mid on for nothing.
On middle, Alam defends it back to the bowler. A maiden over.
Good length ball on off, Rizwan defends it to cover.
Back of a length ball on off, Rizwan goes back in his crease and defends it to the cover region.
Fullish ball on off, Rizwan defends it to silly mid off.
Slower ball on off, Rizwan waits for it and then blocks it to cover.
Well played and well controlled! Short ball around off, Rizwan pulls it with control towards deep mid-wicket for a single.
Very full on the pads, Alam works it down to mid on.
Tossed up outside off, Rizwan pushes it to cover.
Some turn there! Flatter on off, spinning in. Rizwan looks to cut at first but then adjusts and then pushes it to cover.
Just wide of the fielder! Loopy ball on off, Rizwan looks to drive but it goes uppishly. Luckily for Rizwan, it is wide of the fielder at short cover.
On middle, played towards mid on for a single.
Floated on middle, Alam defends it out.
Full on middle, Alam defends it out onto the pitch.
Southee starts with a back of a length ball on middle, Rizwan defends it out onto the pitch.
Full ball outside off, moves away after pitching. Rizwan though shoulders arms to it.
Fuller ball outside off, inviting Rizwan for the drive but Rizwan is not interested and leaves it alone.
EDGY! Rizwan is lucky there. Good length ball on off, Rizwan looks to defend but it takes the inside edge and it goes towards square leg for a single.
EDGY AGAIN! Southee bowls an in-swinger on off, Alam looks to defend but it goes off the outside edge towards gully.
Full ball on off, Alam defends it to cover-point.
Good length ball outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
BEATEN! Lovely ball from Boult! Full ball outside off, moving away. Rizwan looks to defend but the ball whizzes past the outside edge and it goes to the keeper.
Back of a length ball on off, Rizwan defends it to cover.
Fuller ball outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
BEATEN! What a beauty from Boult! Just brilliant! Good length ball around off, Rizwan looks to block but beats the outside edge.
Back of a length ball on off, Rizwan defends it to cover.
Good length ball on the pads, Alam flicks it to deep square leg for a single.
Good length ball outside off, Rizwan watches it carefully and then decides to leave it alone.
Outside off, left alone by Rizwan.
BEATEN! That stays down! Good length ball around off, keeping a little low. Rizwan looks to defend but it sneaks under his bat and goes to Watling.
Fullish ball on off, Rizwan defends it to cover.
Good length ball outside off, Rizwan has no problems in leaving it alone.
Good length ball on the pads, Alam looks to flick but misses and gets hit on the pads.
Good length ball on middle, Alam defends it towards mid on.
Full on middle, worked to mid-wicket.
EDGY FOUR! 100-run stand comes up in a streaky manner but Pakistan won't mind. Good length ball on off, Alam looks to defend but it takes the outside edge and it goes past gully for a boundary.
Length ball on middle and leg, Alam flicks it to deep square leg for a couple.
Good length ball on off, Alam taps it to point.
Good length ball on middle, Rizwan works it to mid-wicket.
Back of a length ball on off, Rizwan blocks it to point.
Nicely played! Good length ball on the pads, Rizwan flicks it through square leg and picks up a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Good length ball on middle, defended out onto the pitch.
Full ball outside off, Rizwan shoulders arms to it.
Length ball on middle, solidly defended back to the bowler.
Full ball on the pads, Alam works it to mid-wicket.
Full ball outside off, Alam lets it go to the keeper.
Short ball around off, Alam pulls it back towards the bowler.
Fullish ball on off, Fawad pushes it to cover.
FOUR! What a shot from Alam! Good length ball outside off, Alam stands tall and then punches it through the cover-point region for a boundary.
Outside off, left alone.
Back of a length ball on middle, Rizwan nudges it to deep square leg for a single.
Back of length ball outside off, Alam leaves it alone.
Full ball outside off, Alam pushes it to cover.
Fuller length outside off, Alam looks to defend but it goes off the inner half of the bat towards mid on.
Good length outside off, Alam leaves that alone.
Length outside off, Alam guides this past gully to collect a run.
Length ball outside off, Alam blocks this out.
Short of a length outside off, Alam bunts this on the off side.
Fuller this time around off, Alam leans on the drive towards mid on and they take three before the fielder returns it back. That was just a mere push but had good timing on that did Alam.
FOUR! Lovely drive.Â Simply superb! Fullish outside off, Rizwan leans into the drive andÂ creams this one through the covers for a boundary.

NOT OUT! It has bounced before going to the keeper! The joy from New Zealand was short-lived. Jamieson runs in and bowls a very full ball outside off, Rizwan looks to drive but it takes the bottom edge and goes to Taylor at first slip. He takes it and New Zealand think that they they haveÂ got their man. Chris Gaffaney was going to give it out but then says wait a minute and wants to have a look upstairs. The soft signal is not out. The replays roll in and the it shows that it has bounced after hitting the bat. Not out will be signal.
Shortish and just around off, jumps off the surface as Rizwan looks to defend. The ball hits the upper part and it goes through gully for a run.
Fuller angling into the pads, Rizwan flicks it wide of mid on and takes a single.
Shortish around off, Alam bunts this down on the off side.
Almost gone! A length ball outside off, bounces and seams away a little away from the batsman.
WIDE! What happened there?Â Everybody is having a laugh out there. Southee runs and bowls a full toss way outside off, Watling collects. Wided.
Around off on a length, kept out.

Bandged short and on middle, Alam pulls it wide of the man at deep square leg. Jamieson there runs to his right and does really well to get down and stop the ball near the fence. They check if it is a clean stop and it is. Two taken.
Fuller and around off, a solid front foot defense.
Fuller ball around off, driven back to the bowler.
Fuller around middle, flicked wide of mid on for a single.
FOUR! Lovely! Short and wide outside off, Alam stands tall and guides this past the gully fielder for a boundary.
FOUR! Back-to-back boundaries! Super shot! A fuller ball around middle, Fawad nails the drive through mid on for a boundary. Moves to 94 now.
Shortish around off, tucked towards mid-wicket.
Length around off, Alam blocks this out.
Short and wide, Rizwan pulls this straight toÂ mid on.
Shortish length around off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
Shortish around middle, Rizwan pulls this towards deep square leg for a run.
Length around middle, played towards covers by Alam.
FOUR BYES! That took off from nowhere! Watling has no chance! Short around middle, Alam looks to pull but misses. Watling, behind the stumps, jumps but fails to collect it.
Length around off, Alam defends this towards covers.
Huge appeal but turned down. Flat and around middle and leg, Rizwan looks to defense but misses to get hit on the pad. They appeal but it is turned down. Looked to be going down leg.
Short and wide outside off, Rizwan goes hard to cut but mistimes it towards point.
Tossd up and outside off, turns away as Rizwan watches it go to the keeper.
FOUR! Rizwan pounces on this short ball. This is on middle, he rocks back and pulls it through mid-wicket for a boundary.
Loopy around off, Rizwan comes on the front foot to block.
Flatter and around off, tucked to mid-wicket for nothing. With that, it is TEA ON DAY 5.
Run straightaway! Fuller and around off, Fawad flicks it wide of the of the man at mid on for one.
FOUR! Runs for Rizwan too! A boundary it is and he moves to 49. Overpitched and outside off, Rizwan leans forward and creams the drive through covers. No one is stopping that.
Good length and around off, Rizwan strokes it to the right of the bowler and Boult gets a hand to it.

FIFTY FOR The SKIPPER! A fuller one around middle, he flicks it to deep square leg to get to the little milestone. Rizwan will know that the job is only half done. But he has led from the front here. Did something similar in the first innings and has done the same again.
Good length and around off, kept out.
Landed around off on a length, Alam defends it out.
FOUR! Runs flowing for Pakistan in this session. Short and wide outside off, Rizwan slashes it over backward point for a boundary. The 150-run stand is up between the two.
This one is banged short and on middle, Rizwan sits under it.
Bouncer around off this time. Once again Rizwan ducks.
Good length and around off, pushed towards point.
Too short again to trouble Rizwan as he ducks.
Down the leg side, tucked to fine leg for one. Rizwan will keep the strike for the next over.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
Fuller and around off, a solid defense offered by Rizwan.
Fuller again, pushed to mid off.
Good stop! Short and wide outside off, Rizwan punches it well but Nicholls dives to his right and makes a fine stop.
Good length and around off, pushed towards gully.
Landed around off, kept out solidly by Rizwan.
Good length and around middle and leg, worked to mid-wicket.
Good length and around middle again, Fawad defends it back to the bowler.
Banged short, Fawad pulls and takes a single to move to 96. He is a boundary away from his ton.
Very full and around off, Rizwan pushes it to mid off.
Length ball around off, pushed towards point for nothing.
Good length ball around off, kept out.
A single! Full and around middle, flicked to fine leg for one.
In the channel outside off, left alone.
FOUR! Slammed! Short and wide outside off, Rizwan drags it from there and slams the pull wide of the man at deep square leg. Santner tries to get around but fails to do so.
Shortish and around off, poked towards the off side.
Lovely delivery from Boult but well defended too. A fuller ball around off, Rizwan pushes it to mid on.
A solid front foot defense on the last ball of the over!

FOUR! CENTURY FOR FAWAD! What a knock! What a player. He has proven his worth here. He was ignored for a number of years, in spite of performing consistently in the domestic arena.Â  Made a comeback eventually against England earlier in the year but got out without scoring in the first innings upon his return. Didn't do much in the next game either but here he is. Got a chance and has bailed his team out ofÂ trouble with a superb century. His second in Tests. The first one came nearly 12 years ago, in his debut game. What a moment. Something to savor for him and every Pakistan fan. Gets to the landmark by slamming this short ball wide of the man at deep mid-wicket. The fielder there ran to his left and dived to stop but missed it. Take a bow, Fawad Alam. Looks at the heavens and celebrates. An emotional moment for him.
Good length and around off, solidly defended.
Watches the next one outside off all the way to the keeper as he shoulders arms.
Good length and around off, a solid block from him. Wagner oversteps.
On off, defended.
NO BALL! Another one! Good length ball outside off, Alam leaves it alone.
Good length ball on off, Alam defends it to the off side.
Good length ball on middle, Alam lets it go to the keeper.
Full ball on middle, Rizwan works it to mid-wicket.
Short ball on middle, Rizwan pulls it to deep square leg for a run.
Short ball around middle, Alam ducks under it.
On a length on middle, Alam tucks it to mid-wicket.
Fullish ball on off, solidly defended out.
Back of a length ball on middle, Alam goes on his back foot and then defends it out.
Fullish ball on off, Rizwan shuffles across and then defends it to point.
Full ball on off, Rizwan drives it to mid off.
Back of a length ball on off, solidly defended onto the pitch.
Good length ball on off, MR pushes it to mid off.
On middle, nudged to mid-wicket.
Just short! Fullish ball outside off, Rizwan drives it uppishly. Luckily for Rizwan, it lands safely in front of the cover fielder.
Full ball on off, keeping a little low. Alam does well to get his bat down in time and defend it out.
On a length on off, Fawad blocks it to cover.
Full ball on middle and leg, Alam flicks it to mid-wicket for a dot.
Short ball around middle, Alam ducks under it.
Another bumper around middle, Alam ducks under it.
Good length ball on middle, Alam works it to mid-wicket.
EDGY! Full ball outside off, Rizwan looks to drive but gets an inside edge onto the pads.
Full ball outside off, Rizwan drives it to mid off for a dot.
On a length on off, Rizwan punches it to mid off.
Slower ball outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
Outside off, Rizwan leaves it alone.
Good length ball outside off, Rizwan shoulders arms to it.Â  26 overs to go in the game. Pakistan need 134 runs.
Fullish ball on middle, Alam pushes it to mid on.
On middle, Alam defends it out.
Short ball outside off, Alam punches it to the off side.
Very full delivery on the pads, Alam flicks it to fine leg and picks up a single.

OUT! LBW! All reds it is and Mohammad Rizwan has to go! End of a wonderful knock from the skipper. New Zealand desperately needed that wicket and they will feel that they have an opening in this game. Can they win this from here? Jamieson bowls a good length ball on middle, Rizwan looks to flick but misses and gets rapped on the pads. New Zealand put up a huge shout for LBW but nothing from the umpire. The Kiwis take the review. The Ultra Edge shows no bat while the Ball Tracker showsÂ all reds. The Kiwis are ecstatic. Pakistan need 133 in 25.1 overs.
Short ball around middle, Ashraf ducks under it.
Full ball on middle, Alam defends it out onto the pitch.
Good length ball on off, Alam defends it to the off side and says no for the single.
On off, Alam bunts this towards cover.
On a length on the pads, Alam looks to flick but gets hit on the thigh pad.
Full ball on middle, Alam plays it back to the bowler.
Good length ball on middle, Fawad is solid in defense.
Fullish on middle, Ashraf pushes it down to mid on.
Good length ball on off, Faheem solidly defends it to cover-point.
Short ball around middle, Ashraf sits under it.

An appeal for LBW turned down! Probably going over the stumps! Short ball around middle and off, Faheem looks to pull but misses and gets hit on the pads. Jamieson appeals but nothing from the umpire. Southee from behind signals that it is high.
Full ball on off, Ashraf defends it out onto the pitch.
Faheem is off the mark! Back of a length ball outside off, Ashraf punches it through the gully region and picks up a couple before the fielder cuts it off.
Full ball on middle, Alam defends it back to the bowler.
Full toss on middle, Alam is shocked as he looks to defend. It hits the upper part of the bat and rolls onto the pitch.
Wagner comes around the wicket and bowls a good length ball on middle, Fawad defends it back to the bowler.
Back of a length ball on middle, Alam blocks it out.
Short ball around middle, Alam ducks under it.

OUT! TAKEN DOWN THE LEG SIDE! Wagner is the man who gets the big wicket. Massive, massive wicket. Wagner bangs it short again and this one is down the leg side. With all the close-in fielders in the sight, Fawad looks to slams it down the leg side. He goes for the pull but ends up gloving it behind. Watling gobbles the chance to his right.Â The marathon knock from Fawad is over. Can termÂ it as a soft dismissal but you got to give it to Wagner. The Kiwi workhorse just kept banging it short. Alam resisted and resisted, almost entire Day 5. But this time around, he went for the shot, maybe to push the fielders back but he pays the price. He walks off with standing ovation from the crowd. A gritty knock comes to an end and New Zealand are in with a big chance now. 22 overs left in the day for them to remove the remaining 4.
Short ball around middle, Ashraf ducks under it.
Back of a length ball on off, Ashraf camps on his back foot and then defends it to the off side.
On middle, solidly defended out.
Short ball on middle, Ashraf pulls it to deep square leg for a single.
Full ball on middle, Yasir defends it back to the bowler.
Full on off, Shah is solid in defense.
FOUR! Faheem is not going to just block. A short ball from Wagner and Faheem swivels and hammers it down to the fine leg fence for a boundary.
Short again and Faheem pulls again. This time he finds the fielder at square leg.
Another short ball but this time Faheem opts to sit under it.
Down the leg side. Faheem looks to flick but misses.
Good length and around off, blocked.

MISFIELD AND FOUR! Full and around off, Faheem strokes it down the ground. Boult runs to his right in anticipation to stop the ball but it lands on one of the footmarks and bounces away from his diving effort. 20 overs remaining in the day.
Short ball on middle, Shah ducks under it.
Full ball on off, Shah defends it to mid off.

OUT! CAUGHT! New Zealand are on fire in the last few overs! Yasir Shah walks off in disappointment. Kyle Jamieson is elated and New Zealand are just three wickets away from a victory.Â  The last few overs have been good for the Kiwis. Jamieson runs in and bowls a short one around off, Yasir Shah has a poke at it. It takes the outside edge and goes towards gully where Tim Southee takes the catch. Pakistan have 19.4 overs to survive in the day.
Full ball on off, Abbas solidly defends it towards mid off.
Shortish ball outside off, Abbas shoulders arms to it.
Back of a length ball on middle, Abbas blocks it to mid on.
Gets hit on the body! Short ball around leg, Ashraf lets it hit him on the arm.
Bouncer around middle, Ashraf ducks under it.

FOUR! Falls in open spaces! Southee goes backwards but it goes over. Short ball around middle, Ashraf pulls it towards deep square leg. Southee, who was standing a little ahead of the fence, tries going back but the ball goes over for a boundary.
Short ball down the leg side, Faheem leaves it alone.

Is that a catch? No, it is not! Very full on off, Afridi defends it towards gully. There is a bit of excitement for a catch but no harm done.

OUT! LBW! Umpire's call it and Pakistan have lost their 9th wicket. This looked plumb but Abbas has to go for the review. Inspired bowling change from Williamson and Santner strikes immediately. Quicker ball on middle and off. Abbas looks to defend but misses and gets hit on the pads. New Zealand appeal and up goes the finger. Abbas reviews. It goes over Santner who takes it with his left hand while in the air. What scenes. The Kiwi players are absolutely ecstatic. NEW ZEALAND WIN BY 101 RUNS.
